author: COMSOL
description:
This example illustrates the principle of wet chemical etching for 2D geometry under laminar flow. Wet chemical etching is particularly important for microelectronics industry for patterning of integrated circuit, MEMS devices,optoelectronic and pressure sensors. This application illustrates wet chemical etching process for copper cavity under an etchant flow of copper chloride. Linear kinetics is assumed for the etching reactant.

Concentration profile, velocity profile and shape evolution of unmasked copper cavity is studied during the etching process. The deforming geometry of copper substrate is found to be dependent on the local fluid velocity profile and on the flux of the etchant species. The model predicts how copper substrate under a laminar flow is etched and tracks the 2D cavity shape during the wet etching process.
